00:53:39.570 --> 00:53:43.911
Q My question's completely silly.
It's related to the Top Chef Masters.

00:53:43.911 --> 00:53:49.550
Do you know how to use a microwave?
When Hubert did not know how to use a microwave,

00:53:49.550 --> 00:53:54.700
we were just -- that's just -- it was -- the
reason I mention this is because, again, my

00:53:54.700 --> 00:54:00.490
wife who doesn't cook at all couldn't even
conceive of someone who was so trained and

00:54:00.490 --> 00:54:04.211
just -- it wasn't part of their lexicon to
use a microwave in their everyday life.

00:54:04.211 --> 00:54:09.770
Rick Bayless: Right. The answer to the question
is -- will become obvious when you think about

00:54:09.770 --> 00:54:14.880
a restaurant kitchen.
If you put a microwave in a restaurant kitchen,

00:54:14.880 --> 00:54:20.220
it gets abused all the time.
Because a customer sends something back and

00:54:20.220 --> 00:54:23.170
it's not hot enough.
Where does it go? Into the microwave.

00:54:23.170 --> 00:54:27.460
Well, as you all know, most food doesn't really
like the microwave very much.

00:54:27.460 --> 00:54:31.410
And so, you just wreck food by throwing it
in a microwave.

00:54:31.410 --> 00:54:38.210
So any very self-respecting restaurant will
not have a microwave in the kitchen because

00:54:38.210 --> 00:54:41.870
of the potential abuse.
If they have one, they will have one only

00:54:41.870 --> 00:54:47.920
in the pastry station and they use it there
for melting butter or melting chocolate, because

00:54:47.920 --> 00:54:51.150
it's a good device for doing that.
So that's the only place that you will see

00:54:51.150 --> 00:54:55.130
it.
We have no microwaves anywhere near our restaurant

00:54:55.130 --> 00:54:58.490
kitchen.
But we have a test kitchen above where we

00:54:58.490 --> 00:55:02.420
have a microwave because, occasionally, we'll
test things for books and stuff like that

00:55:02.420 --> 00:55:05.510
in a microwave.
And so, we need to have one for that.

00:55:05.510 --> 00:55:09.549
But I think, if it weren't for that -- if
